-4-
We're separated by so many miles! One thousand & four hundred miles to date I've driven in a "round-about" way from my dear girl! Of course this is only about 750 miles from you where I am now! Not so bad, but plenty far at that! 
The Auburn has done very well!  You have by this time heard of the speedin' from Fulton MO. to Manhattan Kansas via K.C. MO.! I will get sufficient rest while here in Omaha to make that mile drive from Lincoln Neb. to Kearney Neb. 
Dad will sleep in the rear seat while I travel along thinking about the vacant seat next to me not having my dear girl in it! 
It's saddening to me, but when I think of being back with you soon - then it relieves the pain a lot! 
(over) 

Hope your father's leg is better, & also that Curran will not have to suffer so! 
You know, after a person weakens down to a certain point - they won't suffer so consciously as if not weak! 
I don't know anything more to write about, except that I love you, my sweet girl!! 
I want to be with you so!! 
Always the same 
Endless love,
Your Sig. 
P.S. I have not found any music yet, except a book of modern harmony which is beautiful when used either with classical or popular tunes! S.N. 
